    "name": "Elias Meister",
    "profile": "Born in 1983 in Munich (Germany) guitarist Elias Meister is based in New York city since 2007. His numerous interests in different styles and ways of expression have led him to perform in a broad variety of musical settings. He leads his own groups, such as the Experimental Rock band Spacepilot with Leo Genovese and Joe Hertenstein, that performed at the Moers Festival and the XJAZZ Festival (Berlin) in 2017 and released two vinyls: 'Exophonia' in 2016 and 'Particle Horizon' (Springstoff) in 2018.  He his also founding member of the live Techno and House collective N/UM, that has released two vinyls. In early 2017 Elias Meister joined 28-time Grammy winner Residente's new band, with whom he has toured in Europe, the US, played to sold out stadiums in South America and performed at the 2017 Latin Grammys.\r\nFurthermore he is active as a contemporary jazz musician releasing three Rock-infused Jazz albums: Elias Meister's Miracle Box, Open for Business and Illumi's Journey. He is freelanci",
